WEBVTT

00:01.070 --> 00:04.004
[arrows whooshing]

00:45.735 --> 00:48.876
[slow dramatic music]

01:01.026 --> 01:03.856
[water splashing]

01:57.738 --> 02:00.810
[helicopter whirring]

02:04.089 --> 02:09.094
[shouting in French]
[dog barking]

02:54.381 --> 02:57.418
[shouting in French]

02:59.386 --> 03:00.180
- Don't shoot!

03:00.214 --> 03:01.008
Don't shoot!

03:01.042 --> 03:02.182
I'm not armed!

03:18.681 --> 03:22.132
[men chattering quietly]

03:24.928 --> 03:27.586
[phone ringing]

03:28.725 --> 03:31.556
- I need you to shave
a week off that.

03:31.590 --> 03:32.936
Yeah, all right.

03:34.490 --> 03:35.318
Gentleman.

03:36.250 --> 03:37.147
- We have to talk.

03:38.494 --> 03:40.150
The Canadians.

03:40.185 --> 03:42.705
Their kid got snagged
at the border.

03:42.739 --> 03:43.533
- What, the courier?

03:43.568 --> 03:44.396
- Cedric.

03:44.431 --> 03:45.570
He's all over the news.

03:45.604 --> 03:46.743
- Jesus.

03:46.778 --> 03:47.986
- How the fuck did that happen?

03:48.020 --> 03:50.195
- We don't know how
the fuck that happened.

03:50.230 --> 03:51.472
But apparently
there's a great amount

03:51.507 --> 03:53.992
of anxiety bouncing around now.

03:54.026 --> 03:55.269
- Where are they
holding the kid?

03:55.304 --> 03:57.375
- [Minas] Montreal
detention center.

03:57.409 --> 03:58.962
- Maybe I know
someone inside there.

03:58.997 --> 04:01.413
- Should this Cedric get
an itch to name names-

04:01.448 --> 04:03.519
- No, he's not gonna
name any fucking names.

04:03.553 --> 04:06.591
- Good, because that would
be unpleasant for everyone.

04:08.178 --> 04:10.595
[door slams]

04:15.669 --> 04:18.499
[engine whirring]

04:19.880 --> 04:24.885
[tires screeching]
[intense music]

04:30.718 --> 04:33.721
[door lock chiming]

05:08.860 --> 05:10.482
- What the fuck?
- What?

05:10.517 --> 05:11.414
- I've been in there
for half an hour.

05:11.449 --> 05:12.691
- Yeah, there was traffic.

05:12.726 --> 05:13.830
- Did you recycle at
the Conway off-ramp?

05:13.865 --> 05:15.073
- Yeah, are you
getting paranoid again?

05:15.107 --> 05:16.971
- Don't start with
that paranoid shit.

05:17.006 --> 05:17.903
- Jesus.

05:17.938 --> 05:19.457
Sorry, okay?
- Drive better.

05:19.491 --> 05:21.562
- I'll do my level best.

05:21.597 --> 05:22.908
- I'll be back in an hour.

05:31.814 --> 05:32.746
- Hey.

05:32.780 --> 05:33.678
- Hey.

05:33.712 --> 05:35.162
- Your sister's in the TV room.

05:35.196 --> 05:36.025
- Thanks.

05:37.406 --> 05:41.064
[chattering on TV]

05:41.099 --> 05:42.583
- WOMAN ON TV: Who knows?

05:42.618 --> 05:45.068
Another time, another place.

05:45.103 --> 05:47.485
[indistinct]

05:51.247 --> 05:52.317
- Hey, small fry.

05:55.596 --> 05:57.322
Doctor said you got 19 days.

05:59.704 --> 06:01.878
I'm almost finished
with my deal.

06:02.741 --> 06:03.880
And I figure when we're done,

06:03.915 --> 06:06.262
we can go for a
drive up to the lake.

06:08.022 --> 06:09.127
We can have breakfast.

06:12.544 --> 06:15.236
I mean, fuck, we could
even bring Mom. [chuckles]

06:18.723 --> 06:19.620
What do you think?

06:26.247 --> 06:28.629
[slow music]

06:29.803 --> 06:32.426
She's taking methadone?
- Yes.

06:33.634 --> 06:34.532
- [Jake] Anything else?

06:34.566 --> 06:35.774
- [Doctor] Mild sedatives.

06:35.809 --> 06:36.982
She was violent.

06:37.017 --> 06:38.950
And there's some hearing loss,

06:38.984 --> 06:41.366
about 40% in her right ear.

06:41.401 --> 06:42.574
Hopefully it'll stop.

06:44.058 --> 06:45.612
- Why's that happening?

06:45.646 --> 06:46.509
- [Doctor] We don't know.

06:46.544 --> 06:48.269
We see it sometimes.

06:48.304 --> 06:51.169
We think the opiates damage
the nerves in the ear canals.

07:05.114 --> 07:07.219
- I'm... Claire.

07:07.254 --> 07:08.462
I'm an addict.

07:09.498 --> 07:11.776
Drug of choice, oxy.

07:11.810 --> 07:15.469
Um, I heard Ron talking
about doctor shopping

07:15.504 --> 07:17.575
and it brought back
some nice memories.

07:19.059 --> 07:21.337
Not as good as
the memory of, um,

07:21.371 --> 07:24.478
this one time when I
really needed a fix

07:24.513 --> 07:28.724
and my doctor wouldn't write
me any scripts anymore.

07:28.758 --> 07:29.932
And uh,

07:32.762 --> 07:34.937
I still had the cast from
my original accident,

07:34.971 --> 07:38.630
so I put my wrist in
the car door and I,

07:41.357 --> 07:43.980
so I could, you
know, get a script.

07:45.948 --> 07:48.364
I have an amazing
16-year-old son

07:48.398 --> 07:51.574
and I can't even sit through
a hockey game without...

07:54.715 --> 07:56.027
Without thinking about it.

07:57.200 --> 08:00.997
I would like to be a
better person for him,

08:02.171 --> 08:05.208
and I am working
on that every day.

08:06.278 --> 08:10.559
[slow music]
[phones ringing]

08:10.593 --> 08:14.355
[workers chattering quietly]

08:16.772 --> 08:18.981
Did you bring the slip?

08:19.015 --> 08:20.810
- I did.
- Come here.

08:20.845 --> 08:22.467
- How are you?
- How was school?

08:22.502 --> 08:24.089
- Pretty good.
- Good.

08:25.884 --> 08:26.713
Thank you.

08:29.578 --> 08:32.408
All right, um, your aunt's
coming over for dinner tonight,

08:32.442 --> 08:34.099
so on your way
home from practice,

08:34.134 --> 08:36.136
can you please stop by the store

08:36.170 --> 08:37.862
and pick up some tortillas?

08:37.896 --> 08:39.311
I'm gonna make fajitas tonight.

08:39.346 --> 08:40.692
- Oh, you're cooking?

08:40.727 --> 08:41.935
- Are you teasing?

08:41.969 --> 08:43.177
- You say you're
ordering a pizza?

08:43.212 --> 08:44.489
What did you say?
[Claire laughs]

08:44.524 --> 08:45.352
I'll get them.

08:46.284 --> 08:49.252
- Thank you.
- Love you.

08:49.287 --> 08:50.357
- I love you.

09:00.609 --> 09:02.783
- With our product, Klaralon,

09:02.818 --> 09:04.889
we never cross the
blood-brain barrier,

09:04.923 --> 09:09.445
so we block the receptors from
the reinforcement mechanism

09:09.479 --> 09:13.518
and this greatly diminishes
possibility of addiction.

09:15.451 --> 09:18.903
A patient takes one
dose twice a day

09:18.937 --> 09:21.284
and the incidence of
addictive behavior

09:21.319 --> 09:23.804
is less than a quarter
that of oxycodone.

09:25.185 --> 09:29.638
Klaralon will be the first
truly non-addictive painkiller.

09:29.672 --> 09:34.228
Ladies and gentlemen,
this is the holy grail.

09:34.263 --> 09:37.024
So, let's drink from the cup.

09:37.059 --> 09:39.509
[applauding]

09:43.652 --> 09:45.930
- And what's been
forgotten today,

09:45.964 --> 09:48.518
in our rush to judgment,

09:48.553 --> 09:52.005
is that in the field
of observation,

09:52.039 --> 09:54.870
chance favors the prepared mind.

09:54.904 --> 09:56.768
Now, who said that?

09:56.803 --> 09:59.633
Uh, Alexandra.

09:59.668 --> 10:00.841
- Louis Pasteur.

10:00.876 --> 10:02.843
- Louis Pasteur, he
said that, yes indeed.

10:02.878 --> 10:04.362
And he lived it.

10:04.396 --> 10:09.332
For 30 years, he worked in
pursuit of a singular goal.

10:10.471 --> 10:12.301
Now, many will tell
you that anyone

10:12.335 --> 10:14.924
who works for 30 years on
anything without results

10:14.959 --> 10:18.134
is uh, [laughs] insane.

10:18.169 --> 10:21.966
But isn't the very
definition of insanity here

10:22.000 --> 10:24.278
just another word for focus?

10:24.313 --> 10:26.660
Because without us crazies,

10:26.695 --> 10:28.628
I mean, where
would the world be?

10:28.662 --> 10:29.974
[students laughing]

10:30.008 --> 10:33.080
Okay, what is next?

10:33.115 --> 10:35.151
No, I understand that, Bill.

10:35.186 --> 10:37.326
I just wanna double check
our results here for you,

10:37.360 --> 10:38.879
make sure nothing is off.

10:38.914 --> 10:40.881
- I'm sure your work
is good as usual,

10:40.916 --> 10:43.401
but you know, we're really
getting behind here.

10:43.435 --> 10:45.092
- Just, just bear with me.

10:45.127 --> 10:46.369
Everything will be fine.

10:46.404 --> 10:48.302
- Look, we've given
you a lot of business

10:48.337 --> 10:50.580
over the years, Tyrone, and
you always come through,

10:50.615 --> 10:53.825
but if you want me to
call David Nunez at UCLA

10:53.860 --> 10:55.689
and ask him to pick up
some of the testing work-

10:55.724 --> 10:57.587
- No, no, no, there's
no need for that.

10:57.622 --> 10:59.728
I promise, Bill,
it will be ready.

11:02.489 --> 11:04.008
Hey, Reeva.
- Hey.

11:04.042 --> 11:06.286
- Do you have the results
from the Northlight study?

11:06.320 --> 11:07.528
- Yeah, I'm sorry, Doctor.

11:07.563 --> 11:08.840
I'm just double checking them.

11:08.875 --> 11:10.704
They should be ready by tonight.

11:10.739 --> 11:12.154
- Is everything
all right with it?

11:12.188 --> 11:13.051
- Yeah.

11:13.086 --> 11:14.846
Well, I'll know shortly.

11:14.881 --> 11:17.607
- Okay, well, let me know
as soon as it's done.

11:19.575 --> 11:22.785
- Now, new GS is up from
Washington, name of Garrett.

11:22.820 --> 11:24.649
She wants a full report.

11:24.684 --> 11:26.444
- So, what, you couldn't
explain it to her?

11:26.478 --> 11:28.549
- I could, but she wanted
the agent in charge.

11:28.584 --> 11:30.310
That's you, isn't it?

11:30.344 --> 11:32.001
- What's happening, fellas?
- How you living, Slim?

11:32.036 --> 11:33.347
- Oh, can't complain.

11:33.382 --> 11:34.348
- So, what's the deal?

11:34.383 --> 11:35.902
You know anyone who's
worked with her before?

11:35.936 --> 11:37.800
- Yeah, me, actually, back
when I was in Virginia.

11:37.835 --> 11:38.870
- You did?
[rock music]

11:38.905 --> 11:39.837
Doing what?

11:39.871 --> 11:40.803
- Well, she was a field agent

11:40.838 --> 11:42.494
before she became a supervisor.

11:42.529 --> 11:43.737
- Field agent?

11:43.772 --> 11:45.256
Thought you've always
been a desk jockey.

11:45.290 --> 11:46.533
- I guess there's things

11:46.567 --> 11:48.190
you don't know about me
after all, Mr. Kelly.

11:48.224 --> 11:49.087
- Thank God.

11:49.122 --> 11:50.502
Let's keep it that way.

11:50.537 --> 11:52.712
The operation itself is
pretty straightforward.

11:52.746 --> 11:55.438
We just set up
our own pill mill.

11:55.473 --> 11:57.751
- [Staff Member] That's where
the oxy gets distributed?

11:57.786 --> 11:58.959
- Uh, almost.

11:58.994 --> 12:01.030
No, that's where we hire
the corrupt doctors.

12:01.065 --> 12:02.411
♪ Yeah, you got

12:02.445 --> 12:04.758
These doctors are
really strung out.

12:04.793 --> 12:06.587
They're on their last legs.

12:07.450 --> 12:08.866
And the patients come in

12:08.900 --> 12:10.315
and the doctors write them
a prescription for oxy

12:10.350 --> 12:11.420
whether they need it or not.

12:11.454 --> 12:13.802
[phone ringing]

12:13.836 --> 12:16.183
- Uh, where are these
patients coming from?

12:16.218 --> 12:17.633
- Cappers.

12:17.667 --> 12:19.773
- Those are your recruiters?
- Uh, yes, ma'am.

12:19.808 --> 12:22.293
Like one source we're
developing named Red.

12:22.327 --> 12:24.019
He goes to homeless shelters

12:24.053 --> 12:25.779
and recruits people
to come to our clinic

12:25.814 --> 12:27.574
and pays them $100 a visit.

12:27.608 --> 12:28.955
- Listen, man, you
wanna make some dough?

12:28.989 --> 12:29.783
- Hell yeah.

12:29.818 --> 12:31.302
What you need, bro?

12:31.336 --> 12:33.960
- [Jake] He tries to find
people with Medicare cards,

12:33.994 --> 12:38.136
and then brings them to
us one van load at a time.

12:38.171 --> 12:39.759
♪ Can't you hear me knocking

12:39.793 --> 12:43.038
Patients can even show a dog
x-ray and walk out with pills.

12:43.072 --> 12:44.418
- Looks like you're in bad pain.

12:44.453 --> 12:45.834
You good with oxy 80s?

12:45.868 --> 12:49.078
- And uh, 30 Somas too, right?

12:50.942 --> 12:52.875
- [Garrett] And what about
your partners, the Armenians?

12:52.910 --> 12:56.430
- [Jake] Yeah, Armen Matosyan
and Minas Soghomonyan.

12:56.465 --> 12:58.778
They're AP13, it's
a loose collection

12:58.812 --> 13:00.814
of Armenian power gangsters.

13:00.849 --> 13:03.575
♪ Help me, baby

13:03.610 --> 13:04.645
♪ I ain't no

13:04.680 --> 13:06.337
- Are we selling drugs?

13:06.371 --> 13:07.614
- Uh, no, ma'am.

13:07.648 --> 13:10.444
No, the homeless get the
pills at the pharmacies

13:10.479 --> 13:12.895
and then we buy them back from
them right then and there.

13:12.930 --> 13:15.242
- So, why open up your own mill?

13:15.277 --> 13:16.726
- To buy credibility.

13:16.761 --> 13:18.211
The only way Jake
could get close enough

13:18.245 --> 13:20.972
to the Armenians to build
trust was to show cash flow,

13:21.007 --> 13:23.941
and it took a year of
undercover work to get this far.

13:23.975 --> 13:26.357
- So, $600k of taxpayer money,

13:26.391 --> 13:30.706
you have corrupt doctors,
cappers, and some Armenians.

13:30.740 --> 13:31.949
Why not make a bust?

13:31.983 --> 13:34.020
- Because it's not
about oxy anymore.

13:34.054 --> 13:36.643
The new killer is fentanyl.

13:36.677 --> 13:37.920
And as everyone in this
room already knows,

13:37.955 --> 13:40.405
it's 100 times more
potent than heroin,

13:40.440 --> 13:43.236
and it's being shipped from a
syndicate in China to Canada,

13:43.270 --> 13:44.513
and then smuggled into America

13:44.547 --> 13:46.066
across the wide open border.

13:46.101 --> 13:47.309
- The Armenians control

13:47.343 --> 13:49.621
most of the coastal
city oxy distribution.

13:49.656 --> 13:51.554
Now they wanna control fentanyl.

13:51.589 --> 13:55.041
If Jake can bring the Armenians
and the Canadians together,

13:55.075 --> 13:56.387
we can take everybody down.

13:58.044 --> 13:59.908
♪ I love you, baby

13:59.942 --> 14:03.635
♪ Let it be carried through
the air by the wind ♪

14:03.670 --> 14:07.812
♪ Love is breaking
out all over ♪

14:07.847 --> 14:09.503
♪ It's gonna grow

14:09.538 --> 14:11.747
♪ Till there is no end

14:11.781 --> 14:15.061
♪ Love is breaking
out all over ♪

14:15.095 --> 14:16.752
♪ They're sayin'
♪ I do

14:16.786 --> 14:19.824
♪ I do love you, baby

14:19.859 --> 14:20.929
- [Sam On Phone] Hello?

14:20.963 --> 14:22.758
♪ Yes, I do, I do
- Hi, Sam.

14:22.792 --> 14:23.932
It's David's mom, Claire.

14:23.966 --> 14:25.036
- [Sam On Phone]
Oh, hi, Ms. Reimann.

14:25.071 --> 14:26.486
- Yeah, have you seen David?

14:26.520 --> 14:28.039
- [Sam On Phone] No, I
didn't go to practice today.

14:28.074 --> 14:29.627
- It's just he's not home
yet and I don't know.

14:29.661 --> 14:31.629
- [Sam On Phone] Did
you try the coach?

14:31.663 --> 14:32.975
- No, I'll do that.

14:33.010 --> 14:33.838
Yeah, I'll do that.

14:33.873 --> 14:34.977
- Okay.
- Okay.

14:35.012 --> 14:36.289
Thank you.
- Bye.

14:36.323 --> 14:37.635
♪ The love, love, love, love

14:37.669 --> 14:40.155
♪ Love, baby

14:40.189 --> 14:42.088
- What about the
foundation grant?

14:42.122 --> 14:44.469
- Ah, trust me, you'd
be the first to know.

14:44.504 --> 14:46.368
[laughing]

14:46.402 --> 14:47.887
- Learning to live
with cutbacks,

14:47.921 --> 14:49.095
I suppose there's
an art in that.

14:49.129 --> 14:50.924
- Oh, so I guess that
raise is out, then?

14:50.959 --> 14:53.651
- Nobody is getting a raise.
[Madira laughs]

14:53.685 --> 14:55.342
Well, maybe you are when
you come back this fall

14:55.377 --> 14:56.930
from maternity leave.

14:56.965 --> 14:58.898
- I thought you were gonna
spend time with the baby.

14:58.932 --> 15:00.969
- Well, it's hard for three
to live off love, right?

15:01.003 --> 15:02.246
Geoff's helping a little.

15:02.280 --> 15:04.075
Hopefully he'll help a lot.

15:04.110 --> 15:05.180
- More wine, please.
[laughing]

15:05.214 --> 15:07.492
[phone ringing]

15:07.527 --> 15:09.839
- What kind of artist
would you wanna be, then?

15:09.874 --> 15:12.359
[group chattering quietly]

15:12.394 --> 15:14.154
- Hey, Reeva.
- Hi, Doctor.

15:14.189 --> 15:15.673
Are you still at dinner?
- Yeah.

15:15.707 --> 15:16.812
- [Reeva On Phone] I
finished the study,

15:16.846 --> 15:18.296
but there's something
concerning me.

15:18.331 --> 15:19.884
- Well, what exactly?

15:19.919 --> 15:21.506
- [Reeva On Phone] I'd
rather discuss it in person.

15:21.541 --> 15:22.714
[Tyrone scoffs]

15:22.749 --> 15:24.785
- Can it wait?

15:24.820 --> 15:25.614
- [Reeva On Phone] Not really.

15:25.648 --> 15:26.960
Can you come to the lab?

15:26.995 --> 15:28.548
- What, now?
- I think it'd be best.

15:28.582 --> 15:29.411
- Um.

15:30.308 --> 15:31.758
Yeah.

15:31.792 --> 15:33.070
Yeah, okay.

15:33.104 --> 15:34.588
All right, I'm on my way.

15:35.831 --> 15:37.315
- And I said to the client,

15:37.350 --> 15:39.869
"The most important choice
that you're going to make

15:39.904 --> 15:42.942
to define your brand
is the typography."

15:42.976 --> 15:45.082
And the client looks at the team

15:45.116 --> 15:49.327
and says to us-
[phone vibrating]

15:49.362 --> 15:51.674
- Coach Vogel, hi.

15:51.709 --> 15:52.952
Thank you for calling me back.

15:52.986 --> 15:54.194
- [Coach] Yes, Ms. Reimann.

15:54.229 --> 15:56.058
Yeah, David, he was
at practice today.

15:56.093 --> 15:57.957
He left at around five.

15:57.991 --> 16:00.166
Said he had to stop by
the store on his way home.

16:00.200 --> 16:01.374
- Okay.

16:01.408 --> 16:04.308
Um, and that was the
last you heard from him?

16:04.342 --> 16:05.378
- [Coach] Yes, ma'am.

16:05.412 --> 16:07.345
I'm sure he'll be there soon.

16:07.380 --> 16:08.208
- Thank you.

16:11.625 --> 16:13.006
- [Susan] What?

16:13.041 --> 16:13.834
- I'm going by the store.

16:13.869 --> 16:14.766
- Okay, I'll come.

16:17.562 --> 16:19.185
Would he have gone
to a friend's?

16:19.219 --> 16:20.841
- No.

16:20.876 --> 16:23.879
I mean, I don't know.

16:23.913 --> 16:25.398
- Well, what's he
up to these days?

16:25.432 --> 16:27.745
- Same thing. Sports.

16:28.642 --> 16:30.368
- Anything else?
- Like what?

16:31.473 --> 16:32.992
- I don't know.

16:33.026 --> 16:35.787
- What are you suggesting?
- I'm not saying anything.

16:35.822 --> 16:37.030
- He's a good kid, all right?

16:37.065 --> 16:38.135
- Well, maybe he
has a girlfriend.

16:38.169 --> 16:39.999
- No, he would've told me.

16:44.762 --> 16:47.040
[Jake sighs]

16:47.075 --> 16:48.835
- You've gotta be
fucking kidding me.

16:48.869 --> 16:50.871
- Garrett said it's
time to make some busts.

16:50.906 --> 16:53.115
The president wants a political
win and this could be it.

16:53.150 --> 16:54.461
- So, what, she
can't wait at all?

16:54.496 --> 16:55.911
- She'll pay for two more weeks.

16:55.945 --> 16:58.224
Could you connect the Canadians
and the Armenians by then?

16:58.258 --> 16:59.777
- And find the fentanyl labs,

16:59.811 --> 17:02.573
and take everyone down, dead
to rights, with no support?

17:02.607 --> 17:04.057
- It's either that
or they scuttle it.

17:04.092 --> 17:05.645
You know, she even wanted
the Chinese connection,

17:05.679 --> 17:07.509
but I told her we'd
be chasing ghosts.

17:07.543 --> 17:09.787
- [sighs] Two weeks, um...

17:12.514 --> 17:15.724
Yeah, yeah, I can
make that work.

17:15.758 --> 17:16.552
I gotta get out of here.

17:16.587 --> 17:17.588
I gotta get up there.

17:17.622 --> 17:18.830
Okay, uh, walk me out.
- Yeah.

17:21.730 --> 17:23.421
- Hey, what happened with that
kid up at the border, Cedric?

17:23.456 --> 17:24.905
What the fuck was that?

17:24.940 --> 17:27.080
- Well, RCMP must've
got onto him somehow.

17:27.115 --> 17:28.254
- Yeah, how?

17:28.288 --> 17:29.738
We're the only ones
who knew about the run.

17:29.772 --> 17:31.084
- I don't know, maybe they
have a leak somewhere?

17:31.119 --> 17:32.085
They're not saying much.

17:32.120 --> 17:33.259
- We've worked too hard

17:33.293 --> 17:35.192
to let a bunch of
Mounties fuck this up.

17:35.226 --> 17:36.641
Where are they keeping
the kid anyway?

17:36.676 --> 17:38.712
- Uh, they're moving
him to WITSEC.

17:38.747 --> 17:40.093
He's gonna testify
he was smuggling

17:40.128 --> 17:42.233
on behalf of the
Montreal syndicate.

17:42.268 --> 17:43.993
And that means Mother.

17:44.028 --> 17:45.236
- Fuck.

17:45.271 --> 17:46.341
That means it's only
a matter of time

17:46.375 --> 17:47.549
before Mother gets to him

17:47.583 --> 17:49.275
and anyone else who
knew about this.

17:50.483 --> 17:52.554
- Yeah, Jake, you really
think this is realistic?

17:52.588 --> 17:54.038
I mean, the Montreal piece.

17:54.073 --> 17:56.523
You're right, you don't
have a deep rep with Mother.

17:56.558 --> 17:58.836
Maybe it's dangerous to
press a big sale now.

17:59.975 --> 18:02.081
- Yeah, but what fucking
choice do we have?

18:06.913 --> 18:08.811
- [Cashier] I, I don't know.
- Seriously?

18:08.846 --> 18:10.468
We need to find him.

18:10.503 --> 18:11.814
- So many people
come through here.

18:11.849 --> 18:13.782
- Yeah, so, somebody had
to have seen him, right?

18:13.816 --> 18:14.990
- Ma'am, I don't know.

18:15.024 --> 18:16.164
- Yeah, I know you don't know,

18:16.198 --> 18:17.579
but somebody knows.
- Claire.

18:17.613 --> 18:18.511
- What?

18:18.545 --> 18:19.443
- You've gotta calm down.

18:19.477 --> 18:20.651
- No, I'm not gonna calm down.

18:20.685 --> 18:21.479
- Is everything all right here?

18:21.514 --> 18:22.411
- No.

18:22.446 --> 18:23.516
Everything's not all right.

18:25.173 --> 18:27.899
I'm, I'm looking for my son.

18:27.934 --> 18:28.797
- All right, we wanna help.

18:28.831 --> 18:29.763
We're gonna find him.

18:29.798 --> 18:30.488
All right?
- Thank you.

18:30.523 --> 18:31.351
Thank you.

18:32.214 --> 18:33.388
Sorry, I didn't...

18:33.422 --> 18:34.216
Sorry.

18:35.459 --> 18:38.117
[intense music]

18:47.919 --> 18:51.164
[Tyrone sighs]

18:51.199 --> 18:52.027
- Okay.

18:53.615 --> 18:54.685
This is sugar water.

18:55.824 --> 18:57.066
And where's the drug?

18:57.101 --> 18:59.138
- This is 182 over here.

19:01.485 --> 19:02.348
- Yeah.

19:03.659 --> 19:05.351
I guess Northlight
hasn't quite cracked

19:05.385 --> 19:07.076
that blood-brain issue yet, huh?

19:08.388 --> 19:10.666
Eh, well, they'll
be disappointed.

19:10.701 --> 19:14.187
- Doctor, you asked us to
use Klaralon as a baseline.

19:14.222 --> 19:16.085
- Yeah, yeah, it's
a good control.

19:16.120 --> 19:19.261
- Well, we did, and we ran
it for 10 days as well.

19:25.025 --> 19:25.854
- Uh.

19:26.717 --> 19:28.512
I don't understand you, uh,

19:28.546 --> 19:30.065
you ran 182 twice?

19:30.099 --> 19:33.241
- No, Doctor, this isn't 182.

19:33.275 --> 19:35.484
We gave these mice Klaralon.

19:35.519 --> 19:37.624
This is Klaralon at day 10.

19:49.291 --> 19:51.638
- What the hell is going on?

19:57.955 --> 20:01.234
- We were contracted
to do a 7-day study,

20:01.269 --> 20:03.995
and I elected to use our
standard 10-day protocol

20:04.030 --> 20:06.584
to yield a more
informative result.

20:06.619 --> 20:09.725
Now, everything was fine
throughout the seventh day,

20:09.760 --> 20:13.384
but on day eight, you can
see what started happening.

20:13.419 --> 20:15.144
The mice keep seeking the drug.

20:15.179 --> 20:17.802
They stay only in the
drug dispensing area.

20:17.837 --> 20:19.942
- Until they die.
- Exactly.

20:19.977 --> 20:22.013
You can see from the fMRI scans

20:22.048 --> 20:24.533
that all the addiction centers

20:24.568 --> 20:26.880
in their brains are lighting up.

20:28.054 --> 20:30.263
And then by day
10, they're dead.

20:30.298 --> 20:33.680
That goes for P182 and Klaralon.

20:36.235 --> 20:37.650
- This can't be right.

20:37.684 --> 20:39.168
- Apart from the extra
days of experiment,

20:39.203 --> 20:40.549
everything ran
according to protocol.

20:40.584 --> 20:42.310
- Well, then run it again.

20:42.344 --> 20:44.795
We can't afford to deliver
an unprofessional result.

20:44.829 --> 20:46.348
- I'm sorry, unprofessional?

20:46.383 --> 20:47.625
- Northlight is already into

20:47.660 --> 20:50.110
the final stage of human
trials with Klaralon.

20:51.457 --> 20:53.528
We're just looking into
their new formulation.

20:53.562 --> 20:55.530
There's no way
Klaralon is this toxic,

20:55.564 --> 20:57.946
it's about to be
approved by the FDA!

20:57.980 --> 20:59.327
- We followed the
protocol exactly.

20:59.361 --> 21:00.397
- Then recheck it.

21:01.398 --> 21:03.020
Everything!

21:04.055 --> 21:06.092
The drug, the mice.

21:06.126 --> 21:07.887
Even the damn cages.

21:09.095 --> 21:11.546
Contract research
covers all our funding.

21:11.580 --> 21:14.928
If word gets out that we
don't know what we're doing,

21:14.963 --> 21:17.828
we're, we're done,
we're finished.

21:17.862 --> 21:19.278
- Of course, Doctor.

21:19.312 --> 21:21.349
We ran a standard
replicate study

21:21.383 --> 21:22.660
and it'll be ready
with you first thing.

21:22.695 --> 21:23.799
- Great.

21:23.834 --> 21:25.767
And call me as soon as.

21:31.186 --> 21:31.980
- There.

21:32.014 --> 21:33.153
That's him right there.

21:34.189 --> 21:35.949
- [Manager] That's 5:21 p.m.

21:35.984 --> 21:38.227
Uh, looks like he
bought some tortillas,

21:38.262 --> 21:39.919
hot sauce, paid cash.
- Yeah.

21:42.473 --> 21:44.648
- Can you follow him outside?

21:44.682 --> 21:48.790
- He exited through
the south door,

21:48.824 --> 21:51.206
got on his bike,
looks like, and then.

21:53.967 --> 21:54.761
- And then what?

21:55.659 --> 21:57.212
- I'm afraid that's it.

21:57.246 --> 21:58.834
There's only one camera on
that side of the building.

21:58.869 --> 22:01.147
[phone vibrating]

22:01.181 --> 22:02.010
- Hello?

22:04.978 --> 22:05.807
That's fine.

22:07.326 --> 22:08.637
- What's fine?
- Okay, we'll come now.

22:08.672 --> 22:10.294
Let's go.

22:10.329 --> 22:12.192
They just, um, they-
- What?

22:14.505 --> 22:16.196
- [Police On Radio] Unit
26, this is central.

22:16.231 --> 22:18.751
2-11 in progress, the
corner of Cass and Henry.

22:18.785 --> 22:20.373
Suspect is a male black-
- What is it?

22:20.408 --> 22:21.270
What's going on?

22:22.548 --> 22:23.756
- Are you Ms. Reimann?
- Please tell me

22:23.790 --> 22:26.345
what's going on.
- She's Claire Reimann.

22:26.379 --> 22:28.070
- I'm afraid there's
been an accident.

22:29.382 --> 22:30.625
Your son, David.
- Yeah.

22:32.420 --> 22:33.766
- [Officer] He's gone, ma'am.

22:37.010 --> 22:38.805
- What?

22:38.840 --> 22:40.462
What do you mean?

22:40.497 --> 22:41.463
He's gone where?

22:42.671 --> 22:43.500
- He's dead.

22:45.156 --> 22:45.985
I'm sorry.

22:49.782 --> 22:54.373
[sobbing]
[slow music]

23:22.470 --> 23:27.440
[plane engine roaring]
[intense music]

23:29.787 --> 23:33.964
[muffled speaking
over PA system]

23:48.496 --> 23:51.119
[birds cawing]

23:56.573 --> 24:00.991
[patrons chattering quietly]

24:01.025 --> 24:01.854
- [Jake] Mother?

24:03.718 --> 24:05.409
- Wanna drink something?

24:05.444 --> 24:06.272
A beer?

24:07.204 --> 24:08.688
Labatt?
- Sure.

24:10.518 --> 24:13.659
[Mother speaking French]

24:13.693 --> 24:14.901
Thanks.

24:14.936 --> 24:16.593
Hey, listen, I wanna-
- Wait for the beer.

24:17.801 --> 24:19.458
Correc'?

24:19.492 --> 24:22.564
[muffled rock music]

24:27.776 --> 24:32.781
The way I see it, the
question before us is, why?

24:33.506 --> 24:34.921
Why was the boy
stopped at the border?

24:36.336 --> 24:38.822
And the logical answer is,
someone knew he was crossing.

24:38.856 --> 24:40.237
Now, who knew that?

24:40.271 --> 24:41.997
Your people knew that.

24:42.032 --> 24:43.240
- My guys wouldn't talk.

24:45.656 --> 24:47.727
- Well, somebody
had to tip this off.

24:49.142 --> 24:51.144
It's an unpatrolled stretch
of our southern border.

24:51.179 --> 24:53.457
Can't be caught
without informant.

24:53.492 --> 24:54.941
- But, Mother, my associates,

24:54.976 --> 24:57.357
and you've met them,
they're Armenian.

24:57.392 --> 24:59.808
They would rather die
than talk to the police.

25:01.361 --> 25:02.777
- Look, Jake, I like you.

25:03.778 --> 25:04.986
You've been a good customer,

25:05.020 --> 25:07.160
buying a little
batch here, there,

25:07.195 --> 25:08.541
but this larger plan now

25:08.576 --> 25:11.061
seems to be beyond
your capabilities.

25:11.095 --> 25:12.959
These boys, they
worked well for us

25:12.994 --> 25:14.374
until we delivered to you.

25:14.409 --> 25:15.997
Now we have a bust.

25:16.031 --> 25:17.895
And who knows how many
they're pressuring.

25:17.930 --> 25:19.448
- Okay, I agree.

25:19.483 --> 25:20.691
Things haven't necessarily
gone smoothy so far, but-

25:20.726 --> 25:22.348
- Smooth?

25:22.382 --> 25:23.591
Are you stupid or what?

25:23.625 --> 25:25.178
[Mother speaking French]

25:25.213 --> 25:27.836
- Maybe for now you
keep your head down,

25:27.871 --> 25:29.113
focus on what you know.

25:30.874 --> 25:32.427
- Couriers aren't the only way.

25:33.877 --> 25:37.018
My guys run trucks through
the entire United States.

25:37.052 --> 25:38.606
So, you take the
product to a warehouse,

25:38.640 --> 25:40.849
you package it as vitamins,

25:40.884 --> 25:44.232
then they come in their
trucks and pick it up.

25:44.266 --> 25:47.131
- Well, tell me,
what's gonna happen

25:47.166 --> 25:48.547
when they get to customs?

25:50.134 --> 25:50.963
- NAFTA.

25:52.136 --> 25:53.448
You take it to a
Foreign Trade Zone

25:53.482 --> 25:55.346
where the police
can't do inspections,

25:55.381 --> 25:57.383
only customs agents can,

25:57.417 --> 25:58.626
and they're not gonna open

25:58.660 --> 26:00.282
every single bottle
of sealed vitamins.

26:03.044 --> 26:07.048
- Before we trust, as your
President Reagan used to say,

26:07.082 --> 26:08.359
we must verify.

26:09.671 --> 26:11.949
We must learn why it did happen.

26:11.984 --> 26:13.917
[Guy speaking French]

26:13.951 --> 26:15.712
- Oui.

26:15.746 --> 26:17.679
We're gonna talk to
our guy at customs.

26:22.615 --> 26:23.547
- It's right there.

26:45.189 --> 26:46.639
- [Doctor] You sure?

26:46.674 --> 26:47.502
- Yeah.

26:54.267 --> 26:58.651
[gasps]
[slow music]

27:07.453 --> 27:11.112
- [sobbing] Oh, god.

27:11.146 --> 27:13.079
- We won't have
toxicology for a few days,

27:13.114 --> 27:15.841
but a paramedic in the alley
said it was an overdose.

27:16.738 --> 27:17.601
Oxycodone.

27:19.707 --> 27:20.915
- What?

27:20.949 --> 27:21.847
- [Detective Carson] He
was foaming at the mouth

27:21.881 --> 27:23.365
when they arrived.

27:23.400 --> 27:25.402
They tried Narcan to revive
him, but it was too late.

27:27.646 --> 27:30.372
Were you aware of any
issues with your son?

27:30.407 --> 27:31.442
- [Claire] Like what?

27:31.477 --> 27:32.547
- Drug issues.
- No.

27:34.998 --> 27:36.689
Absolutely not.

27:36.724 --> 27:38.346
- Any idea where
he would get pills?

27:38.380 --> 27:41.625
- Uh, my, my sister had
an accident a while ago.

27:41.660 --> 27:42.799
- Sue.

27:42.833 --> 27:43.385
- And there were some
painkillers lying-

27:43.420 --> 27:44.628
- Sue.

27:44.663 --> 27:45.836
- There were some
painkillers around.

27:45.871 --> 27:47.389
- Those pills have
been gone for months.

27:47.424 --> 27:49.357
- [Detective Carson] Sometimes
children steal these pills.

27:49.391 --> 27:51.842
- David wasn't doing
drugs, I would've known.

27:51.877 --> 27:53.050
- [Detective Carson]
I understand.

27:53.085 --> 27:54.811
Is it a single parent household?

27:54.845 --> 27:56.295
- What are you getting at?

27:56.329 --> 27:57.537
Just come out and say it to me.

27:57.572 --> 28:00.195
Otherwise what are
you gonna do about it?

28:00.230 --> 28:02.508
- We're gonna continue
to monitor the situation.

28:02.542 --> 28:03.992
- And?

28:04.027 --> 28:05.166
- [Detective Carson] And
see if anything comes up.

28:05.200 --> 28:06.408
- What does that mean?
- I, I, Claire-

28:06.443 --> 28:07.340
- No, what does that...

28:07.375 --> 28:08.514
What the fuck does that mean,

28:08.548 --> 28:09.722
see if anything comes up?

28:09.757 --> 28:11.344
Are you out there looking?

28:11.379 --> 28:13.519
I'm sorry, I love you so much.

28:14.762 --> 28:16.004
- [Detective Carson]
Right now the department

28:16.039 --> 28:18.075
is treating this as
an accidental death.

28:18.110 --> 28:19.836
- Accidental?

28:19.870 --> 28:21.596
You don't even
know what happened.

28:22.942 --> 28:25.393
- Ms. Reimann, we have
40 overdoses this week,

28:25.427 --> 28:27.119
here in Detroit alone.

28:27.153 --> 28:28.914
That's more than homicides.

28:28.948 --> 28:31.226
This isn't anything
against your son.

28:31.261 --> 28:32.400
It's a terrible drug.

28:33.573 --> 28:34.402
I'm sorry.

28:36.231 --> 28:38.613
We have his belongings for you.

28:38.647 --> 28:40.339
We just need you
to sign for them.

28:41.236 --> 28:44.308
[slow intense music]

29:23.934 --> 29:25.971
- [Reeva] So, this is the
replicate study I brought in,

29:26.005 --> 29:28.490
and it shows exactly
the same result.

29:28.525 --> 29:30.009
- Biological explanation?

29:30.044 --> 29:33.116
- We'd need a mass spec to see
how the liver's metabolizing,

29:33.150 --> 29:35.394
not to mention many
more basic experiments.

29:35.428 --> 29:37.361
- We're talking six
months of work at least.

29:37.396 --> 29:40.364
- Mm, that's not gonna
fly with Northlight.

29:41.296 --> 29:42.781
[sighs]

29:42.815 --> 29:45.300
Something in the drug is
crossing the blood-brain barrier

29:45.335 --> 29:46.992
and hitting the reward centers,

29:47.026 --> 29:51.548
but Klaralon is supposed
to reduce dependence,

29:51.582 --> 29:53.274
not increase it threefold.

29:54.551 --> 29:56.346
How could they not
have caught this?

29:57.761 --> 29:59.314
Well, write up your findings.

29:59.349 --> 30:01.800
We should get this over
to Northlight right away.

30:14.191 --> 30:17.574
- [Guy] How did the border
agents know to stop the boy?

30:17.608 --> 30:18.437
- You tell me.

30:19.645 --> 30:21.958
- You're supposed to be
our ears of the patrols.

30:24.236 --> 30:26.272
- I heard rumors.
- What?

30:29.724 --> 30:32.002
- Someone's talking,
in your house.

30:32.037 --> 30:33.452
[Guy scoffs]

30:33.486 --> 30:35.730
- That's ridiculous.
[Fournier speaking French]

30:35.764 --> 30:36.765
- It's true.

30:36.800 --> 30:37.594
There's a list.

30:38.975 --> 30:40.597
- What list?

30:40.631 --> 30:41.943
- And who are you?
- Never mind that.

30:41.978 --> 30:43.117
Answer the fucking question.
- Hey, whoa.

30:43.151 --> 30:44.843
Whoa, relax.

30:44.877 --> 30:46.741
You know a guy named Davison?

30:46.775 --> 30:50.227
The cop that was disgraced,
facing corruption charges?

30:50.262 --> 30:51.435
- [Guy] Yeah.

30:51.470 --> 30:52.920
- When Internal
Affairs got onto him,

30:52.954 --> 30:55.612
they heard about a list he kept
at the major crimes bureau,

30:55.646 --> 30:58.270
Over 200 names on it.

30:58.304 --> 31:02.274
Every informant from every
crew he ever worked with.

31:02.308 --> 31:05.864
I bet that on that
list is your informant.

31:06.865 --> 31:08.349
- Where's the list now?

31:08.383 --> 31:09.626
- [Fournier] I heard
he's trying to sell it.

31:09.660 --> 31:10.558
- Where?

31:10.592 --> 31:11.973
- I'm just a custom inspector.

31:12.008 --> 31:13.699
Can't you find him?

31:13.733 --> 31:15.114
- All right, get out.

31:15.149 --> 31:16.426
[Fournier speaking French]

31:16.460 --> 31:19.532
Get the fuck out!
[groaning]

31:21.051 --> 31:23.674
See, I told you, he's garbage.

31:23.709 --> 31:25.884
- We gotta find that list.

31:28.714 --> 31:31.096
[slow music]

32:07.408 --> 32:10.066
[sighs heavily]

32:11.550 --> 32:13.724
[sobbing]

32:16.210 --> 32:19.040
[phone vibrating]

32:50.899 --> 32:52.729
- [Meg Voicemail] Hi,
this is Dr. Meg Holmes.

32:52.763 --> 32:53.902
Please leave a message.

32:55.249 --> 32:57.596
- So, in recognition
of that great bounty,

32:57.630 --> 33:00.392
our foundation is pleased
to announce tonight

33:00.426 --> 33:04.465
a five-year $30
million commitment

33:04.499 --> 33:07.778
to the building of this
new contemporary art wing.

33:07.813 --> 33:10.229
[applauding]

33:12.956 --> 33:14.509
- Once FDA approves,

33:14.544 --> 33:18.513
we will bring Klaralon
to market in six months.

33:18.548 --> 33:19.894
And in the spirit of gift giving

33:19.928 --> 33:21.482
you demonstrated tonight,

33:21.516 --> 33:24.002
here on page three are
the sales projections.

33:26.073 --> 33:27.660
- Wow, those are, uh...

33:27.695 --> 33:28.868
Wow.

33:28.903 --> 33:31.871
- Physician response
is tremendous.

33:31.906 --> 33:33.528
- When our dad built Northlight,

33:33.563 --> 33:35.082
his dream was not
just to make money,

33:35.116 --> 33:37.670
it was to make the
world a better place.

33:37.705 --> 33:40.570
- An addiction-free painkiller
was always his goal,

33:40.604 --> 33:41.502
and you found it.

33:42.710 --> 33:45.126
- You've done our
family proud, Meg.

33:45.161 --> 33:48.026
- It was only possible through
your support, gentlemen.

33:49.165 --> 33:51.477
I'm pleased we were
able to deliver for you.

33:51.512 --> 33:53.479
[phone vibrating]

33:53.514 --> 33:54.446
- Will you excuse me?

33:54.480 --> 33:55.343
- Of course.
- Sure.

33:57.794 --> 33:59.106
- Hello?

33:59.140 --> 34:00.831
- [Bill On Phone]
Meg? It's Bill.

34:00.866 --> 34:01.832
We've got an issue.

34:06.320 --> 34:08.943
- [Meg] How long has
he been a resource?

