- Yeah.

1:09:46.285 --> 1:09:48.149
- His name is Guy Broussard.

1:09:48.184 --> 1:09:49.909
He's the number two
of the operation.

1:09:49.944 --> 1:09:51.428
Works for a man called Mother.

1:09:52.671 --> 1:09:54.155
- Mother?

1:09:54.190 --> 1:09:56.330
- Yeah.
- That's his name?

1:09:56.364 --> 1:09:58.228
- Real name is Claude Veroche.

1:09:59.574 --> 1:10:01.404
He owns a bar called La Marina.

1:10:06.685 --> 1:10:08.238
- [Claire] This is
the man in charge?

1:10:08.273 --> 1:10:10.309
- He looks like a
respectable citizen, right?

1:10:10.344 --> 1:10:12.242
The file tells a
different story.

1:10:12.277 --> 1:10:15.556
Been arrested for
distribution, manufacturing.

1:10:15.590 --> 1:10:17.903
Did four years for manslaughter.

1:10:17.937 --> 1:10:20.457
He's also been linked to
several unsolved homicides.

1:10:20.492 --> 1:10:21.941
- What about the other thing?

1:10:24.081 --> 1:10:25.497
- It's a ghost gun.

1:10:25.531 --> 1:10:26.705
It's untraceable.

1:10:26.739 --> 1:10:28.327
Safety's on the trigger,
so if I were you-

1:10:28.362 --> 1:10:29.880
- I know how to shoot.

1:10:31.088 --> 1:10:31.882
- Good.

1:10:32.987 --> 1:10:34.782
What are you planning
to do, exactly?

1:10:38.130 --> 1:10:38.924
- Thank you.

1:10:41.789 --> 1:10:42.583
You can go now.

1:10:44.723 --> 1:10:46.242
- [Investigator] You be careful.

1:11:00.463 --> 1:11:03.293
[engine whirring]

1:11:04.536 --> 1:11:05.778
- [Stan On Phone]
Jake, what's up?

1:11:05.813 --> 1:11:07.504
- Yeah, I got a plate for you.

1:11:07.539 --> 1:11:12.302
Michigan plate, 23458
QV, Quebec Victor.

1:11:12.337 --> 1:11:13.130
Run the ownership
records on that.

1:11:13.165 --> 1:11:14.339
Tell me what you find.

1:11:14.373 --> 1:11:15.443
- [Stan On Phone] Yeah,
I'll do it right now.

1:11:15.478 --> 1:11:16.996
- All right.

1:11:17.031 --> 1:11:19.861
[engine whirring]

1:11:25.660 --> 1:11:28.180
[gun cocking]

1:11:29.561 --> 1:11:32.805
- The owner is Claire
Reimann, an architect.

1:11:32.840 --> 1:11:36.326
Couple of arrests, one for
possession, one for DUI.

1:11:36.361 --> 1:11:38.639
- Narcotics possession?
- Yeah.

1:11:38.673 --> 1:11:40.917
Uh, hold on, there's
something else.

1:11:40.951 --> 1:11:42.263
Oh, her son just died.

1:11:42.298 --> 1:11:43.851
OD'd on oxy.

1:11:43.885 --> 1:11:45.128
- Jesus.

1:11:45.162 --> 1:11:46.094
- Yeah, she was
making some noise

1:11:46.129 --> 1:11:47.475
about wanting an investigation.

1:11:47.510 --> 1:11:49.028
- Was her son
involved in anything?

1:11:49.063 --> 1:11:50.582
- [Stan On Phone]
Uh, don't know.

1:11:50.616 --> 1:11:52.169
They think he was clean.

1:11:52.204 --> 1:11:52.998
- Well, what's his deal?

1:11:53.032 --> 1:11:54.171
Any interests?

1:11:54.206 --> 1:11:56.829
- A sports star,
looking at scholarships.

1:11:56.864 --> 1:11:58.175
- Wait a minute.

1:11:58.210 --> 1:11:59.453
Winter sports?

1:11:59.487 --> 1:12:00.316
- [Stan On Phone] Jesus.

1:12:00.350 --> 1:12:01.558
Cedric!
- Yeah.

1:12:01.593 --> 1:12:03.249
What do you wanna bet
they knew each other?

1:12:13.190 --> 1:12:15.538
- You know I didn't
harass anybody.

1:12:15.572 --> 1:12:17.816
That is all Northlight.

1:12:17.850 --> 1:12:19.714
- We can't have any contact
until the tenure hearing.

1:12:19.749 --> 1:12:21.060
It's against the rules.

1:12:21.095 --> 1:12:22.476
- Dragging my name
through the mud,

1:12:22.510 --> 1:12:23.856
is that part of the rules?

1:12:23.891 --> 1:12:25.030
- Keep your voice down.

1:12:27.101 --> 1:12:27.929
Come with me.

1:12:34.660 --> 1:12:35.834
Your whole goddamn career,

1:12:35.868 --> 1:12:37.111
you basically just
took the money

1:12:37.145 --> 1:12:39.527
and you, you, you
stamped it all through.

1:12:39.562 --> 1:12:40.528
Isn't that about right?

1:12:40.563 --> 1:12:42.185
And now you grow a conscience.

1:12:42.219 --> 1:12:44.118
People here like you!
- Yeah, except maybe you.

1:12:44.152 --> 1:12:46.189
- That is so unfair.
- Don't you get

1:12:46.223 --> 1:12:47.777
what Northlight is doing?

1:12:47.811 --> 1:12:52.091
This is the biggest public
health crisis since tobacco!

1:12:52.126 --> 1:12:53.748
We can't just turn a blind eye!

1:12:53.783 --> 1:12:55.129
- We can't weather it!

1:12:55.163 --> 1:12:57.476
We barely have enough
funding to get by.

1:12:57.511 --> 1:12:58.753
You understand that?

1:12:58.788 --> 1:13:00.548
And I'm responsible for
thousands of students,

1:13:00.583 --> 1:13:01.998
and faculty, and-
- Oh, Geoff,

1:13:02.032 --> 1:13:04.621
this drug is gonna
fucking kill people.

1:13:04.656 --> 1:13:07.417
Just like oxy,
just like fentanyl!

1:13:07.452 --> 1:13:09.005
- You don't know that!
- You don't see it, do you?

1:13:09.039 --> 1:13:10.282
You don't see it.

1:13:10.316 --> 1:13:12.698
This just doesn't go
back in the bottle.

1:13:12.733 --> 1:13:14.631
- We're a university,
we're not the FDA.

1:13:14.666 --> 1:13:16.253
It's not our responsibility-

1:13:16.288 --> 1:13:17.910
- Then whose is it?

1:13:20.879 --> 1:13:22.570
- Sign what it is they want.

1:13:22.605 --> 1:13:24.192
Maybe you'll get your lab back.

1:13:25.470 --> 1:13:26.643
Get your life back.

1:13:30.475 --> 1:13:32.062
Don't throw it all away, Tyrone.

1:13:33.685 --> 1:13:34.996
You're not gonna win this.

1:13:36.308 --> 1:13:38.724
[door slams]

1:13:40.519 --> 1:13:43.280
[mixer clanking]

1:13:52.842 --> 1:13:53.843
- This is the mixer.

1:13:54.982 --> 1:13:57.225
It blends the powder
base with the fentanyl.

1:13:59.469 --> 1:14:01.091
This one takes the
fentanyl powder

1:14:01.126 --> 1:14:02.610
and presses it into pills.

1:14:03.749 --> 1:14:05.164
This is the counter machine.

1:14:07.373 --> 1:14:09.445
Pills go in, pills go out

1:14:10.618 --> 1:14:12.862
and drop directly into
your vitamin bottle.

1:14:12.896 --> 1:14:15.589
Street value is $30 per pill.

1:14:15.623 --> 1:14:16.659
- That's impressive.

1:14:19.213 --> 1:14:22.043
[Mother coughing]

1:14:23.528 --> 1:14:24.908
- What's your situation now?

1:14:26.082 --> 1:14:27.739
- My guys will be
here in three days.

1:14:27.773 --> 1:14:28.602
- Good.

1:14:29.465 --> 1:14:30.466
So, now you've seen.

1:14:31.950 --> 1:14:32.985
We're gonna be ready.

1:14:34.849 --> 1:14:37.611
Oh, and also, uh,

1:14:37.645 --> 1:14:40.165
we took care of
that other problem.

1:14:40.199 --> 1:14:41.615
- What problem?

1:14:41.649 --> 1:14:43.099
- Cedric.

1:14:43.133 --> 1:14:44.031
The courier.

1:14:44.963 --> 1:14:47.068
- Yeah?
- Yep.

1:14:47.103 --> 1:14:48.380
- That son of a bitch is gone.

1:14:48.414 --> 1:14:49.864
- Yeah. [laughs]

1:14:49.899 --> 1:14:54.490
We also found out who the
informant was after all.

1:14:55.732 --> 1:14:56.733
- [Guy] Oh, you did?

1:14:58.701 --> 1:15:00.496
- [Mother] Oui.

1:15:00.530 --> 1:15:01.358
- Good, good.

1:15:02.532 --> 1:15:03.499
And who was it?

1:15:06.053 --> 1:15:09.677
- Well, [chuckles]
you knew all along,

1:15:09.712 --> 1:15:11.299
it was you, Tabernac!

1:15:11.334 --> 1:15:13.129
[gunshot]

1:15:13.163 --> 1:15:13.957
[gun cocking]

1:15:13.992 --> 1:15:17.064
[shouting in French]

1:15:18.928 --> 1:15:22.518
He killed Davison in the hotel
room before you got there.

1:15:22.552 --> 1:15:25.382
He stole the laptop because
he knew his name was on it.

1:15:27.212 --> 1:15:28.938
He was an RCMP snitch.

1:15:30.111 --> 1:15:30.940
- How, how-

1:15:30.974 --> 1:15:32.182
[speaks in French]

1:15:32.217 --> 1:15:33.045
Here.

1:15:34.115 --> 1:15:35.013
We went to his house.

1:15:35.047 --> 1:15:36.462
We find the laptop there.

1:15:37.325 --> 1:15:38.879
But your name wasn't on it.

1:15:40.674 --> 1:15:42.572
That was good news
for you, my friend.

1:15:44.125 --> 1:15:46.058
But now you know the stakes.

1:15:47.473 --> 1:15:51.167
Anything happens, we can touch
you anywhere in the world,

1:15:51.201 --> 1:15:52.513
no matter who you are.

1:15:54.619 --> 1:15:57.173
So, are we still on?

1:15:59.106 --> 1:16:01.764
- Yeah.
[intense music]

1:16:14.984 --> 1:16:17.158
[banging]

1:16:45.980 --> 1:16:48.983
[doorknob jiggling]

1:16:49.950 --> 1:16:52.884
[glass shattering]

1:16:53.885 --> 1:16:56.577
[lock clicking]

1:17:35.927 --> 1:17:38.515
[door opening]

1:17:40.172 --> 1:17:42.830
[Claire groans]

1:17:44.107 --> 1:17:44.936
- Fuck.

1:17:47.524 --> 1:17:48.767
- [Claire] Sit down, now!

1:17:51.805 --> 1:17:52.702
- Please don't shoot me.

1:17:52.737 --> 1:17:54.117
- Did you have my son killed?

1:17:54.152 --> 1:17:57.293
- Please don't shoot.
- Did you have my son killed?

1:17:57.327 --> 1:17:58.984
- Who?
- David.

1:17:59.019 --> 1:18:00.814
David Reimann.

1:18:05.163 --> 1:18:07.510
- I told them he
didn't know anything.

1:18:07.544 --> 1:18:09.339
He just came along on one run.

1:18:09.374 --> 1:18:11.445
- You had my son
run drugs for you?

1:18:11.479 --> 1:18:12.308
- No.

1:18:13.827 --> 1:18:16.381
It wasn't like that.
- Then what was it like?

1:18:16.415 --> 1:18:17.727
Huh?

1:18:17.762 --> 1:18:19.211
- We met at camp.

1:18:19.246 --> 1:18:21.213
I asked him to come along
on a trip with some friends.

1:18:21.248 --> 1:18:23.388
I hid the pills in David's bag.

1:18:23.422 --> 1:18:25.424
He never even knew
what he was carrying.

1:18:35.607 --> 1:18:38.437
- So, then, why
did they kill him?

1:18:39.438 --> 1:18:40.785
Why not you?

1:18:40.819 --> 1:18:41.993
- I don't know!

1:18:42.027 --> 1:18:43.339
I didn't know they were
gonna kill anybody.

1:18:43.373 --> 1:18:45.651
- You didn't know who
was gonna kill anybody?

1:18:47.377 --> 1:18:48.206
- Mother.

1:18:49.138 --> 1:18:50.691
Word is after Cedric got busted,

1:18:50.726 --> 1:18:52.003
he got completely paranoid

1:18:52.037 --> 1:18:53.418
and started cutting loose ends.

1:18:53.452 --> 1:18:54.833
I'm probably next.

1:18:58.526 --> 1:19:00.805
Please don't shoot me.

1:19:00.839 --> 1:19:01.702
Please.

1:19:03.428 --> 1:19:04.256
Please.

1:19:18.546 --> 1:19:19.927
[water running]

1:19:19.962 --> 1:19:22.067
[grunts]

1:19:31.214 --> 1:19:34.045
[phone vibrating]

1:19:36.841 --> 1:19:39.050
- Is it true?
- Is what true?

1:19:39.084 --> 1:19:40.845
- Did they kill the kid?

1:19:40.879 --> 1:19:42.225
Cedric.

1:19:42.260 --> 1:19:43.433
- I'm afraid so.

1:19:43.468 --> 1:19:44.710
They found him
foaming at the mouth

1:19:44.745 --> 1:19:45.642
at the foot of his cell.

1:19:45.677 --> 1:19:46.816
Somebody got to his food.

1:19:48.197 --> 1:19:50.233
There's another
kid dead here, too.

1:19:50.268 --> 1:19:51.856
- What kid?

1:19:51.890 --> 1:19:53.478
- Simon Gilcrest.

1:19:53.512 --> 1:19:55.721
OD'd on oxy like
the Reimann boy.

1:19:55.756 --> 1:19:56.757
We don't know how
they're linked yet.

1:19:56.792 --> 1:19:58.517
He was probably another courier.

1:19:58.552 --> 1:20:01.003
We think they all
went to the same camp.

1:20:01.037 --> 1:20:01.900
- [Jake] Guy's dead, too.

1:20:01.935 --> 1:20:02.832
- [Stan On Phone] What?

1:20:02.867 --> 1:20:03.902
How?
- Mother.

1:20:04.869 --> 1:20:06.008
Just now.

1:20:06.042 --> 1:20:08.493
I was fucking standing
right next to him.

1:20:08.527 --> 1:20:10.667
- [Stan On Phone] I think
we reconsider the meet.

1:20:11.841 --> 1:20:12.738
- No.

1:20:12.773 --> 1:20:13.878
- Jake, remember what happened

1:20:13.912 --> 1:20:15.396
when Benny Alvarez
messed with these guys?

1:20:15.431 --> 1:20:16.777
They're still pulling pieces
of his body out of the river.

1:20:16.812 --> 1:20:18.399
- Do you think I don't
fucking know that?

1:20:18.434 --> 1:20:19.849
Huh?

1:20:19.884 --> 1:20:21.023
Do you have any idea
what I just went through?

1:20:21.057 --> 1:20:22.334
- They're doing
multiple homicides.

1:20:22.369 --> 1:20:24.440
You cannot walk
into that buy alone.

1:20:24.474 --> 1:20:26.235
- Mother said that-
- Fuck Mother!

1:20:26.269 --> 1:20:27.546
Is he worth your life?

1:20:32.931 --> 1:20:33.829
- We can't quit.

1:20:35.900 --> 1:20:37.453
We can't stop.

1:20:39.765 --> 1:20:41.008
- At least let me have

1:20:41.043 --> 1:20:42.596
some advance warning
to cover you, okay?

1:20:42.630 --> 1:20:43.597
Even 40 minutes.

1:20:45.702 --> 1:20:46.496
- Okay, yeah.

1:20:47.981 --> 1:20:49.499
I'll text you the meet
location as soon as I get it,

1:20:49.534 --> 1:20:51.191
and you coordinate with RCMP.

1:20:51.225 --> 1:20:53.400
But they can't fuck this up.

1:20:53.434 --> 1:20:55.160
- [Stan On Phone] I'm on it.

1:20:55.195 --> 1:20:57.645
- Okay, and be flexible.

1:20:57.680 --> 1:20:59.544
The meet location could
change at any minute.

1:21:03.341 --> 1:21:05.308
- [Madira] I went
by the school today.

1:21:05.343 --> 1:21:07.345
Why didn't you tell
me what was happening?

1:21:09.209 --> 1:21:12.488
[Tyrone sighs heavily]

1:21:16.733 --> 1:21:17.873
- I'm sorry, I...

1:21:19.184 --> 1:21:21.152
I tried to take care of it, and,

1:21:23.257 --> 1:21:24.569
it got so much bigger.

1:21:27.883 --> 1:21:30.920
I guess I overestimated myself.

1:21:32.094 --> 1:21:33.854
- But why didn't you
share it with me?

1:21:34.959 --> 1:21:35.925
Do you think I
couldn't handle it?

1:21:35.960 --> 1:21:36.926
- No, no.

1:21:36.961 --> 1:21:39.204
[stammers]

1:21:40.481 --> 1:21:42.207
I didn't wanna worry you.

1:21:42.242 --> 1:21:43.760
I wanted to protect you.

1:21:43.795 --> 1:21:44.900
- Oh, come on.

1:21:46.453 --> 1:21:47.799
We're in this together.

1:21:49.076 --> 1:21:51.182
And you have a responsibility.

1:21:51.216 --> 1:21:53.287
- Yeah, to our family.

1:21:53.322 --> 1:21:55.324
- To something larger than that.

1:21:58.914 --> 1:22:02.745
- If they let me go now,
under these circumstances,

1:22:02.779 --> 1:22:05.748
I just can't turn around
and find another job.

1:22:08.854 --> 1:22:10.408
I really don't know what to do.

1:22:11.685 --> 1:22:13.514
- We will manage.

1:22:13.549 --> 1:22:14.515
We will.

1:22:16.172 --> 1:22:17.104
We always do.

1:22:18.450 --> 1:22:19.279
- Yeah?

1:22:28.184 --> 1:22:29.013
I'm sorry.

1:22:43.682 --> 1:22:44.511
Um, Bill.

1:22:45.512 --> 1:22:48.170
It's, uh, Tyrone.

1:22:50.068 --> 1:22:52.312
I've thought about
your proposal.

1:22:52.346 --> 1:22:53.899
Um.

1:22:53.934 --> 1:22:55.867
Uh, let's come to
an arrangement.

1:23:02.322 --> 1:23:04.980
[paper ripping]

1:23:17.233 --> 1:23:19.925
[phone ringing]

1:23:26.380 --> 1:23:28.969
[Claire sighs]

1:23:30.419 --> 1:23:31.868
- Hello?

1:23:31.903 --> 1:23:34.423
- [Susan On Phone] Claire,
I've been trying to call you.

1:23:34.457 --> 1:23:36.080
Your car's not in the driveway.

1:23:36.114 --> 1:23:36.977
Where are you?

1:23:38.082 --> 1:23:38.944
- I'm traveling.

1:23:38.979 --> 1:23:39.773
- Traveling?

1:23:39.807 --> 1:23:40.705
Where?

1:23:40.739 --> 1:23:41.913
- [Claire On Phone] Listen, Sue,

1:23:41.947 --> 1:23:43.777
I can't really talk
right now, okay?

1:23:43.811 --> 1:23:45.503
I-
- What are you doing, Claire?

1:23:47.988 --> 1:23:49.783
- Sue.
- Claire.

1:23:50.784 --> 1:23:53.131
I know that this is hell.

1:23:53.166 --> 1:23:54.063
- You know,

1:23:55.754 --> 1:23:57.135
the doctor said it took

1:23:59.724 --> 1:24:02.451
four minutes for his
heart to give out.

1:24:05.419 --> 1:24:07.559
It took him four minutes
to stop breathing.

1:24:09.044 --> 1:24:13.151
Four minutes his heart was
constricting in his chest,

1:24:13.186 --> 1:24:15.947
like someone was strangling
him until he died.

1:24:19.330 --> 1:24:22.229
[sobbing]
- Claire.

1:24:22.264 --> 1:24:23.575
- [Claire On Phone] I'm sorry.

1:24:23.610 --> 1:24:24.473
- Claire.

1:24:24.507 --> 1:24:25.336
Claire.

1:24:26.164 --> 1:24:28.787
[Claire gasps]

1:24:50.154 --> 1:24:52.846
[water running]

1:25:06.170 --> 1:25:07.412
- Dr. Brower.
- Yes.

1:25:07.447 --> 1:25:08.620
- How are you?

1:25:08.655 --> 1:25:09.759
I'm Sarah, Dr.
Simons' assistant.

1:25:09.794 --> 1:25:10.726
- Hi.
- Follow me, please.

1:25:10.760 --> 1:25:12.072
- Thank you.

1:25:12.107 --> 1:25:13.591
- Did you find everything okay?

1:25:13.625 --> 1:25:14.488
- Yeah, thanks.

1:25:17.871 --> 1:25:20.218
It's uh, quite a place, huh?

1:25:20.253 --> 1:25:21.150
- [Sarah] Yeah.

1:25:21.185 --> 1:25:22.600
I'm lucky to call it my office.

1:25:34.059 --> 1:25:34.888
- [Bill] Tyrone.

1:25:35.854 --> 1:25:36.683
- [Tyrone] Bill.

1:25:38.202 --> 1:25:39.893
- These are the
execution copies.

1:25:41.066 --> 1:25:44.208
And here is the grant
check for your lab.

1:25:47.901 --> 1:25:49.144
- It's made out to me.

1:25:50.593 --> 1:25:51.974
- I'm sure you can
endorse it over,

1:25:52.008 --> 1:25:53.734
if that's what you want.

1:25:53.769 --> 1:25:54.597
It's up to you.

1:25:57.462 --> 1:25:58.601
- Dr. Brower.

1:26:01.570 --> 1:26:03.537
I am Meg Holmes.

1:26:03.572 --> 1:26:04.435
- Dr. Holmes.

1:26:05.988 --> 1:26:07.023
Yeah.

1:26:07.058 --> 1:26:08.024
The CEO.

1:26:09.025 --> 1:26:11.200
