1:33:54.180 --> 1:33:55.043
- Where's Mother?

1:33:56.009 --> 1:33:57.252
- Don't worry about it.

1:33:57.286 --> 1:33:58.425
You're dealing with us.

1:34:01.118 --> 1:34:02.291
- No.

1:34:02.326 --> 1:34:03.638
No Mother, no deal.

1:34:08.573 --> 1:34:09.436
- Jake!

1:34:11.128 --> 1:34:12.094
Where you going?

1:34:13.233 --> 1:34:15.132
- What is this, a joke?

1:34:15.166 --> 1:34:17.513
[Mother speaking French]

1:34:17.548 --> 1:34:18.791
- Come back here.

1:34:25.729 --> 1:34:29.111
[Mother speaking French]

1:34:34.772 --> 1:34:37.292
- Is this everything?
- Mm-hmm.

1:34:38.327 --> 1:34:39.915
- Do you mind?
- Mm.

1:34:55.655 --> 1:34:58.485
[bottle rattling]

1:35:13.638 --> 1:35:14.467
Okay.

1:35:16.641 --> 1:35:18.264
Where's the rest?

1:35:18.298 --> 1:35:20.300
- What, you don't trust
me anymore, Mother?

1:35:22.337 --> 1:35:24.304
- This is Montreal, my friend.

1:35:25.167 --> 1:35:27.791
Strange things happen here.

1:35:27.825 --> 1:35:29.068
- That's $1 million.

1:35:29.102 --> 1:35:30.552
That's my deposit,
like we discussed.

1:35:30.586 --> 1:35:31.380
Now what's gonna happen is-
[guns cocking]

1:35:31.415 --> 1:35:33.382
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

1:35:33.417 --> 1:35:34.729
I'm reaching for my phone.

1:35:35.695 --> 1:35:37.248
All right, everybody calm down.

1:35:38.871 --> 1:35:40.493
Now I text my guys.

1:35:40.527 --> 1:35:43.289
- All right, we move when
they come in with the cash.

1:35:43.323 --> 1:35:45.601
- Then they're gonna park
two trucks down at the end

1:35:45.636 --> 1:35:46.602
and your goons are
gonna help them

1:35:46.637 --> 1:35:48.052
load up all these pallets.

1:35:48.087 --> 1:35:50.434
After that-
[rumbling]

1:35:50.468 --> 1:35:51.642
[Mother speaking French]

1:35:51.676 --> 1:35:52.988
- Tell your man to
stand down, right now.

1:35:53.023 --> 1:35:54.231
- I want a better view

1:35:54.265 --> 1:35:55.335
if we're gonna send
our guys in there.

1:35:55.370 --> 1:35:56.716
- You heard that?

1:35:56.751 --> 1:35:57.544
[indistinct]

1:35:57.579 --> 1:35:58.753
Check it out.

1:35:58.787 --> 1:35:59.857
- What the hell is
going on here, Mother?

1:35:59.892 --> 1:36:01.479
- We wait one minute, okay?

1:36:01.514 --> 1:36:02.998
- No, no more minutes.

1:36:03.033 --> 1:36:05.483
My guys come in and we
do the switch right now!

1:36:07.520 --> 1:36:12.525
[gunshots]
[shouting in French]

1:36:13.112 --> 1:36:15.804
[gunshot]

1:36:15.839 --> 1:36:17.219
[sirens blaring]

1:36:17.254 --> 1:36:18.289
- Go, go, go!

1:36:18.324 --> 1:36:21.776
Go out!
[shouting in French]

1:36:21.810 --> 1:36:26.781
[Mother speaking French]
[officers speaking French]

1:36:30.646 --> 1:36:33.304
[Jake groaning]

1:36:41.485 --> 1:36:43.728
[gunshots]

1:36:45.661 --> 1:36:48.733
[shouting in French]

1:37:02.886 --> 1:37:06.475
[officers speaking French]

1:37:21.939 --> 1:37:24.804
[Jake groaning]

1:37:24.839 --> 1:37:27.082
[gunshots]

1:37:29.326 --> 1:37:32.639
- [Stan] Freeze, motherfucker!

1:37:32.674 --> 1:37:34.883
[gunshots]

1:37:37.023 --> 1:37:41.510
- No!
[gunshots]

1:37:44.168 --> 1:37:45.066
Fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck.

1:37:45.100 --> 1:37:46.722
[Stan groaning]

1:37:46.757 --> 1:37:47.862
No, no, no.

1:37:47.896 --> 1:37:48.690
No, no, no.

1:37:48.724 --> 1:37:49.518
No!

1:37:49.553 --> 1:37:50.692
Look at me, it's okay!

1:37:50.726 --> 1:37:51.520
Man down!

1:37:51.555 --> 1:37:52.383
Man down!

1:37:53.695 --> 1:37:54.903
Oh, goddamn.

1:37:54.938 --> 1:37:56.042
Help!

1:37:56.077 --> 1:37:56.905
Help!

1:38:12.714 --> 1:38:15.786
- The division takes the
opioid crisis very seriously.

1:38:16.960 --> 1:38:18.444
As the president
himself has said,

1:38:18.478 --> 1:38:21.481
there is no greater scourge
facing America from within.

1:38:21.516 --> 1:38:22.827
- Well, I still fail to see

1:38:22.862 --> 1:38:24.864
how a breakthrough
drug, like Klaralon,

1:38:24.899 --> 1:38:26.866
despite the purported
implications

1:38:26.901 --> 1:38:28.833
of Dr. Brower's so-called tests-

1:38:28.868 --> 1:38:30.801
- Mr. Chairman, respectfully,

1:38:30.835 --> 1:38:32.907
Dr. Brower's implications
are more than purported.

1:38:32.941 --> 1:38:34.494
- According to Dr.
Brower's own report,

1:38:34.529 --> 1:38:36.082
he exceeded the
study parameters.

1:38:36.117 --> 1:38:37.497
- And that's precisely
why he was able

1:38:37.532 --> 1:38:38.878
to find the results he did.

1:38:38.913 --> 1:38:40.328
I think we should
hear from Dr. Brower.

1:38:40.362 --> 1:38:41.812
- One moment, please.

1:38:41.846 --> 1:38:43.055
- Okay, are we talking about
a [indistinct] shutdown?

1:38:43.089 --> 1:38:45.402
[indistinct]

1:38:45.436 --> 1:38:47.162
- What's going on?
- I don't know.

1:38:49.337 --> 1:38:51.546
- Thank you, Dr. Brower,
that won't be necessary.

1:38:51.580 --> 1:38:53.065
The division has
discussed the matter

1:38:53.099 --> 1:38:54.618
and is prepared to
make a decision.

1:38:54.652 --> 1:38:55.826
- Mr. Chairman, I object
to a decision without-

1:38:55.860 --> 1:38:58.311
- That's enough, Mr. Walker.

1:38:58.346 --> 1:39:00.589
The division has
read the evidence

1:39:00.624 --> 1:39:02.695
and it is our position
that the benefits

1:39:02.729 --> 1:39:06.354
of the item outweigh
these potential risks.

1:39:06.388 --> 1:39:10.151
FDA approval for
Klaralon will proceed.

1:39:10.185 --> 1:39:12.291
Northlight Pharmaceuticals
will arrange a fund

1:39:12.325 --> 1:39:14.051
for further studies of addiction

1:39:14.086 --> 1:39:15.984
in the amount of $11 million.

1:39:16.019 --> 1:39:17.296
Do you all agree?

1:39:17.330 --> 1:39:18.159
- [Division Members] Agreed.

1:39:18.193 --> 1:39:19.677
- Mr. Chairman.

1:39:19.712 --> 1:39:21.921
Mr. Chairman, at
least let me speak!

1:39:21.956 --> 1:39:23.267
- Sorry, Dr. Brower.

1:39:23.302 --> 1:39:24.579
Meeting is adjourned.

1:39:25.960 --> 1:39:28.341
[slow music]

1:39:30.274 --> 1:39:33.898
[group chattering quietly]

1:39:58.958 --> 1:40:00.132
- What happened?

1:40:00.166 --> 1:40:01.685
- I've been reassigned.

1:40:03.307 --> 1:40:05.930
[Tyrone sighs]

1:40:11.902 --> 1:40:13.041
- So, that's it?

1:40:13.076 --> 1:40:13.938
It's over?

1:40:15.250 --> 1:40:17.252
There's gotta be another way.

1:40:18.357 --> 1:40:20.117
- I've been thinking.

1:40:20.152 --> 1:40:21.532
There's someone you can talk to,

1:40:21.567 --> 1:40:24.052
but without the
committee's protection,

1:40:24.087 --> 1:40:26.710
you'd have to violate
your non-disclosure.

1:40:26.744 --> 1:40:27.711
- And?

1:40:27.745 --> 1:40:29.402
- And if it goes
bad for you now,

1:40:29.437 --> 1:40:32.060
we're talking debts
surviving bankruptcy.

1:40:32.095 --> 1:40:34.476
You'd probably still be
paying in the afterlife.

1:40:37.031 --> 1:40:38.377
- Well, I got nothing now,

1:40:39.826 --> 1:40:42.553
so what difference
would it make?

1:40:44.038 --> 1:40:46.971
[bubbling]

1:40:47.006 --> 1:40:50.665
[Emmie breathing heavily]

1:40:50.699 --> 1:40:51.493
- Jake.

1:40:53.047 --> 1:40:54.255
It's your sister.

1:40:57.637 --> 1:41:02.194
I just wanted to say I'm
really sorry for the other day,

1:41:03.298 --> 1:41:08.062
and I'm feeling much better now.

1:41:12.859 --> 1:41:13.826
I love you so much.

1:41:24.768 --> 1:41:26.080
- [RCMP Chief] We're
still ID-ing the bodies,

1:41:26.114 --> 1:41:27.184
but from what we can tell,

1:41:27.219 --> 1:41:29.221
they were low-level muscle.

1:41:29.255 --> 1:41:31.119
No traffickers.

1:41:31.154 --> 1:41:32.327
- What about Mother?

1:41:32.362 --> 1:41:34.329
- Apparently he's got
some family in Algiers,

1:41:34.364 --> 1:41:35.779
so we put some men
on the airports,

1:41:35.813 --> 1:41:38.506
but we're not gonna
see him again.

1:41:38.540 --> 1:41:40.059
How about the Armenians?

1:41:40.094 --> 1:41:43.131
- Prosecutor says he doesn't
have enough to charge them.

1:41:43.166 --> 1:41:44.305
- What?

1:41:44.339 --> 1:41:45.306
- They never set
foot in the building,

1:41:45.340 --> 1:41:46.548
let alone the lot.

1:41:46.583 --> 1:41:48.688
There's no overt act.

1:41:48.723 --> 1:41:50.690
- We'll issue a Red
Notice for Mother,

1:41:50.725 --> 1:41:53.762
but beyond that my superiors
wanna terminate cooperation.

1:41:53.797 --> 1:41:55.799
- Yeah, mine too.

1:41:55.833 --> 1:41:56.627
- So, that's it?

1:41:57.594 --> 1:41:58.974
You're just gonna quit?

1:41:59.009 --> 1:41:59.906
- Calm down, Jake.

1:41:59.941 --> 1:42:01.805
- Two crown officers are dead.

1:42:01.839 --> 1:42:04.704
My department won't risk
any more loss of life.

1:42:04.739 --> 1:42:05.809
I'm sorry.

1:42:12.850 --> 1:42:13.851
- Agent Kelly.

1:42:16.958 --> 1:42:17.959
- What?

1:42:17.993 --> 1:42:19.167
What do you want me to say?

1:42:19.202 --> 1:42:20.582
What do you want from me?

1:42:20.617 --> 1:42:23.516
- I want you to calm
down and be professional.

1:42:23.551 --> 1:42:24.552
- Professional what?

1:42:24.586 --> 1:42:26.105
Agent or drug dealer?

1:42:27.175 --> 1:42:28.521
You realize how fucked this is?

1:42:28.556 --> 1:42:29.936
- Yeah, I do.

1:42:29.971 --> 1:42:32.732
I'm the one who had
to call Stan's wife.

1:42:32.767 --> 1:42:34.148
He was my friend, too.

1:42:37.530 --> 1:42:38.359
- I'm sorry.

1:42:39.532 --> 1:42:41.293
- What do you think
we're here to do?

1:42:41.327 --> 1:42:42.811
To make a difference?

1:42:42.846 --> 1:42:44.986
- So, what are we here to do?

1:42:45.020 --> 1:42:46.470
- Our job.

1:42:46.505 --> 1:42:48.852
As mandated by the people.

1:42:48.886 --> 1:42:52.131
- So, we're just here
to clean up, is that it?

1:42:52.166 --> 1:42:54.375
I don't accept that.

1:42:54.409 --> 1:42:55.583
- That's not fair, Jake.

1:42:57.101 --> 1:42:58.896
You're a good agent.

1:42:58.931 --> 1:43:00.691
We fight the best we can.

1:43:02.728 --> 1:43:04.626
- I'll see you at the airport.

1:43:04.661 --> 1:43:07.767
[slow intense music]

1:43:09.942 --> 1:43:10.770
- Fuck.

1:43:19.089 --> 1:43:20.401
- [Jim] Hello, Ms. Reimann?

1:43:20.435 --> 1:43:23.231
This is Jim Douglas,
Douglas Investigations.

1:43:23.266 --> 1:43:26.993
I'm just following up on that
individual that we spoke of.

1:43:27.028 --> 1:43:27.994
You asked me to let you know

1:43:28.029 --> 1:43:30.342
if I had any new information.

1:43:30.376 --> 1:43:33.966
Well, I think you might
be interested in this.

1:44:01.718 --> 1:44:04.099
- Where's Mother?
[bartender speaking French]

1:44:04.134 --> 1:44:06.378
I will blow your head all
over this fucking bar.

1:44:06.412 --> 1:44:07.586
Where's Mother?

1:44:07.620 --> 1:44:09.243
- [speaking French]
I don't know!

1:44:11.175 --> 1:44:12.660
- Last chance.

1:44:12.694 --> 1:44:15.835
- He keeps a seaplane by
the Dwyer shipping yard.

1:44:15.870 --> 1:44:17.043
That's all I know.

1:44:17.078 --> 1:44:18.597
- If I find out
you're lying to me-

1:44:18.631 --> 1:44:19.736
- It's the truth!

1:44:19.770 --> 1:44:20.875
I swear it!

1:45:58.144 --> 1:45:58.973
- Mother!

1:46:03.115 --> 1:46:06.049
[gunshots]

1:46:06.083 --> 1:46:08.741
[Claire groans]

1:46:12.193 --> 1:46:12.987
- Hey, hey, hey.

1:46:13.021 --> 1:46:14.402
Hey.
- What?

1:46:14.437 --> 1:46:15.921
- It's okay, hey, relax.

1:46:15.955 --> 1:46:17.025
Relax, relax.
- Get away from me!

1:46:17.060 --> 1:46:17.854
- I'm a federal agent.

1:46:17.888 --> 1:46:18.786
I'm a federal agent.

1:46:18.820 --> 1:46:19.649
It's okay.

1:46:20.546 --> 1:46:21.409
It's okay.

1:46:21.444 --> 1:46:22.376
It's okay.

1:46:22.410 --> 1:46:23.894
Let me see.

1:46:23.929 --> 1:46:24.826
Fuck. Okay.

1:46:24.861 --> 1:46:25.827
It just went through your arm.

1:46:25.862 --> 1:46:26.759
You're gonna be okay.

1:46:26.794 --> 1:46:27.726
Come on.

1:46:27.760 --> 1:46:30.418
[Claire groans]

1:46:32.972 --> 1:46:33.801
It's okay.

1:46:34.871 --> 1:46:35.941
There you go.

1:46:45.571 --> 1:46:46.641
Stay right here.

1:46:46.676 --> 1:46:48.574
I'll be right back.
[exhales]

1:47:28.234 --> 1:47:30.409
[gunshot]

1:48:01.475 --> 1:48:04.408
[doorbell ringing]

1:48:10.380 --> 1:48:11.277
- [Geoff] Already?

1:48:12.658 --> 1:48:16.282
- [Tyrone] The university
gave us three days to vacate.

1:48:16.317 --> 1:48:19.009
- Where to?
- I don't know.

1:48:20.597 --> 1:48:22.634
- How long did we
work together, Tyrone?

1:48:22.668 --> 1:48:23.876
- A long time.

1:48:23.911 --> 1:48:27.328
- And in that time,
didn't I support you,

1:48:27.362 --> 1:48:31.539
and champion your labs,
and find you grant money

1:48:31.574 --> 1:48:32.989
wherever the hell I could,

1:48:34.128 --> 1:48:36.199
help keep your whole
field of research alive?

1:48:36.233 --> 1:48:39.236
- Yeah, yeah, you
did all of that.

1:48:39.271 --> 1:48:42.481
- Whatever I did, I never
compromised our university.

1:48:42.516 --> 1:48:44.069
And I never compromised
our students.

1:48:44.103 --> 1:48:46.692
- Geoff, all you
did was compromise.

1:48:46.727 --> 1:48:49.937
You had the facts and you
just didn't look at them.

1:48:49.971 --> 1:48:52.905
You stood there while
they made you complicit.

1:48:52.940 --> 1:48:56.081
- I spent a lifetime
building that school.

1:48:56.115 --> 1:48:58.566
That I should take a
moment before deciding

1:48:58.601 --> 1:48:59.809
whether or not to destroy it

1:48:59.843 --> 1:49:01.604
supporting your
half-baked research

1:49:01.638 --> 1:49:03.088
against a drug monolith.

1:49:03.122 --> 1:49:04.330
- What about the people,

1:49:04.365 --> 1:49:06.229
the ones that we're
supposed to serve,

1:49:06.263 --> 1:49:08.265
the ones who can't
speak for themselves?

1:49:14.651 --> 1:49:16.411
- It's the Detroit Evening News.

1:49:19.311 --> 1:49:21.106
You gave them the
whole story, huh?

1:49:22.625 --> 1:49:24.661
Even everything that
happened between us.

1:49:25.628 --> 1:49:26.905
I thought we were friends.

1:49:27.871 --> 1:49:28.700
- So did I.

1:49:30.356 --> 1:49:31.426
- You know this isn't gonna make

1:49:31.461 --> 1:49:33.428
a damn bit of difference
to Northlight.

1:49:34.568 --> 1:49:36.604
They've got their approval.

1:49:36.639 --> 1:49:38.157
They'll still put
their drug out.

1:49:38.192 --> 1:49:39.538
- But the people will know.

1:49:40.919 --> 1:49:42.472
They'll know.

1:49:42.506 --> 1:49:44.025
And that's the best I could do.

1:49:46.441 --> 1:49:48.616
- I've been asked to resign.

1:49:48.651 --> 1:49:49.444
- I'm sorry.

1:49:50.342 --> 1:49:51.895
- Me, too.

1:49:51.930 --> 1:49:53.587
If I could do it all over again.

1:49:55.623 --> 1:49:56.451
Oh.

1:49:57.660 --> 1:50:00.248
What difference does it make?

1:50:00.283 --> 1:50:01.215
Bye, Tyrone.

1:50:08.291 --> 1:50:10.707
[slow music]

1:50:26.136 --> 1:50:29.139
- Hopefully it looks
like two gangsters

1:50:29.174 --> 1:50:31.107
killed each other
for a million dollars

1:50:32.418 --> 1:50:33.799
and no one looks any deeper.

1:50:36.699 --> 1:50:38.286
- Didn't you say you were a cop?

1:50:39.529 --> 1:50:40.323
- I was.

1:50:42.946 --> 1:50:45.224
- [Claire] So are you
taking me to prison now?

1:50:49.988 --> 1:50:50.782
- No.

1:50:52.128 --> 1:50:52.922
- Why not?

1:50:57.823 --> 1:50:59.376
- You remind me of someone.

1:51:03.001 --> 1:51:05.003
[Claire gasps]
- Sorry.

1:51:05.037 --> 1:51:05.866
I'm sorry.

1:51:08.006 --> 1:51:12.079
- [exhaling] I don't understand.

1:51:13.252 --> 1:51:15.530
So, what am I
supposed to do now?

1:51:19.845 --> 1:51:20.674
- I don't know.

1:51:39.520 --> 1:51:40.348
- Thank you.

1:51:51.187 --> 1:51:53.327
- And given the doctor's
ongoing press schedule

1:51:53.361 --> 1:51:55.053
that you may have heard about,

1:51:55.087 --> 1:51:56.779
if any of you ever get out

1:51:56.813 --> 1:51:59.022
of your labs long enough
to read the paper,

1:51:59.057 --> 1:51:59.954
[students laughing]

1:51:59.989 --> 1:52:01.887
we were very lucky to get him.

1:52:01.922 --> 1:52:04.959
So, I hope you'll all
join me in welcoming

1:52:04.994 --> 1:52:07.203
our new co-chair of biology

1:52:07.237 --> 1:52:09.757
here at University of Michigan.

1:52:09.792 --> 1:52:13.243
Dr. Tyrone Brower.
[applauding]

1:52:15.729 --> 1:52:16.730
- Thank you!

1:52:19.387 --> 1:52:22.874
Thank you, and welcome to
my class... [intense music]

1:56:18.247 --> 1:56:21.836
[intense electronic music]
